  <div class="container-md">
    <h1 class="h3">Language learning is hard and will always be hard.</h1>

    <p>Deep down, we already know it. That's why we're so surprised when someone we've known for years suddenly starts speaking in a foreign language. This rarely happens.</p>

    <blockquote class="call-out">
      Thousands of hours of practice and thousands of words to learn.
    </blockquote>

    <p>To reach the fluency level (B2 in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_European_Framework_of_Reference_for_Languages" class="link-secondary" target="_blank">CEFR</a> terms), a person must:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Study and practice for between 1,000 and 3,000 hours</li>
      <li>Learn between 6,000 and 8,000 words</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Thousands of hours of practice and thousands of words are no joke. It takes years to accomplish &ndash; that's why so many people give up, and that's why there are so few people fluent in three or more languages.</p>

    <blockquote class="call-out">
      Successful language learners are active language users.
    </blockquote>

    <p>Those who understand the enormous scope of language learning don't rely on apps and courses &ndash; they incorporate a foreign language into their lives. They use every opportunity to practice the language:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>They read books</li>
      <li>Consume news</li>
      <li>Watch YouTube</li>
      <li>Listen to podcasts</li>
      <li>They think in a foreign language</li>
      <li>They jump on every opportunity to use the foreign language in their lives</li>
    </ul>

    <p>They start doing that as soon as they reach a stable A2 level. It's hard, but they persevere and eventually become fluent.</p>

    <blockquote class="call-out">
      Becoming fluent in a foreign language improves life.
    </blockquote>

    <p>Pursuing fluency in a foreign language tangibly improves people's lives. They become better articulated. They find better jobs, better friends, and better spouses. They move to better countries.</p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">Vocably is designed for such people. For those who know that language learning is no joke.</p>

